					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Lord Nightmare wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Technicality: does it reload when it HITS 0 (on 1-&gt;0 transition, so 0 is only in timer for an irerelevantly small time period before reload) or does it reload on underflow FROM 0 (0-&gt;"-1" transition)?<br /><br />LN</div>
<br />
<br />when it hits 0, the NEXT clock performs a reload.  so, the counter would count like so:
<br />
<br />if the reload is 10h...
<br />
<br />(reset)
<br />10
<br />10
<br />10
<br />(counter enabled)
<br />0f
<br />0e
<br />0d
<br />0c
<br />...
<br />02
<br />01
<br />00
<br />10
<br />0f
<br />0e
<br />0d
<br />0c
<br />
<br />when the counter is reloaded, the IRQ flag would be set also.
<br />
<br />02  0
<br />01  0
<br />00  0
<br />10  1
<br />
<br />the second number being the IRQ flag.</div>

					
