					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you want the header readable on the NES, then how are you going to handle Unicode UTF-8 character encoding? A player running on an NES would have to include a font covering the whole Unicode BMP including CJK, a layout engine including stacked accents, bidirectional reordering, and contextual glyph replacements, just in case an NSF has Arabic song titles.
<br />
<br />"Engine" is known for any game whose music data format has been described on romhacking.net. For example, a lot of Capcom games use substantially the same engine.</div>

